{layout 'base.latte'}

{block title}fhooe/router-skeleton: 404 – Not Found{/block}

{block main}
    <h2>404 – Not Found</h2>
    <p>This is the 404 view.</p>
    <p>It is displayed when a route not defined in the router is accessed. It also returns HTTP status code 404,
        which you can see in the console of your dev tools.</p>

    <div class="alert alert-warning">
        <h4>No styles?</h4>
        <p>If you see this page without any styles and instead of the index page, your router setup needs to be fixed.
            Your base path might need to be set correctly or set in the first place. Go to index.php and use
            <code class="user-select-all">$router->setBasePath("/path/to/fhooe-router-skeleton/public");</code> to set
            it according to the location of your project to your webserver's web root.</p>
    </div>
{/block main}